<main>

  <!-- BREADCRUMB -->
  <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb">
    <div class="breadcrumb-inner">
      <a href="/">Home</a> &rsaquo; <span>Blog</span>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="blog-hero">
    <div class="blog-hero-inner">
      <h1>Texas Special Education Blog</h1>
      <p>Practical guides, actionable tips, and the latest updates to help Texas families navigate ARD meetings, IEPs, evaluations, and parent rights.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FILTER BAR -->
  <div class="filter-bar">
    <div class="filter-bar-inner" role="tablist" aria-label="Filter blog posts by category">
      <button class="category-tag active" data-filter="all" role="tab" aria-selected="true">All Posts</button>
      <button class="category-tag" data-filter="ard-meetings" role="tab" aria-selected="false">ARD Meetings</button>
      <button class="category-tag" data-filter="evaluations" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Evaluations</button>
      <button class="category-tag" data-filter="iep-goals" role="tab" aria-selected="false">IEP Goals</button>
      <button class="category-tag" data-filter="parent-rights" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Parent Rights</button>
      <button class="category-tag" data-filter="district-updates" role="tab" aria-selected="false">District Updates</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- BLOG CONTENT -->
  <section class="blog-section">
    <div class="blog-inner">

      <!-- No results -->
      <div class="no-results" style="display:none;">
        <p>No posts in this category yet. Check back soon &mdash; new articles are published monthly.</p>
        <button class="category-tag" data-filter="all" style="margin-top:1rem;">View All Posts</button>
      </div>

      <!-- FEATURED POST -->
      <div class="featured-post" data-category="evaluations">
        <span class="featured-label">Featured</span>
        <h2><a href="/blog/what-to-do-when-school-denies-evaluation.html">What to Do When Your Texas School District Denies an Evaluation Request</a></h2>
        <p>If your district denied your child's evaluation request, don't panic. Texas law gives you specific options — from requesting Prior Written Notice to filing a TEA complaint. Here's exactly what to do next, step by step.</p>
        <a class="read-more" href="/blog/what-to-do-when-school-denies-evaluation.html">Read the full guide &#8594;</a>
      </div>

      <!-- BLOG GRID -->
      <div class="blog-grid">

        <!-- Card 1 -->
        <article class="blog-card" data-category="ard-meetings">
          <div class="blog-card-image">🏫</div>
          <div class="blog-card-body">
            <div class="blog-card-meta">
              <span>January 8, 2026</span>
              <span class="tag">ARD Meetings</span>
            </div>
            <h3><a href="/blog/10-questions-to-ask-at-ard-meeting.html">10 Questions Every Texas Parent Should Ask at Their ARD Meeting</a></h3>
            <p>Walking into an ARD meeting without a plan is like showing up to court without a lawyer. These 10 questions will help you stay focused and get answers.</p>
            <a class="read-more" href="/blog/10-questions-to-ask-at-ard-meeting.html">Read more &#8594;</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Card 2 -->
        <article class="blog-card" data-category="evaluations">
          <div class="blog-card-image">📋</div>
          <div class="blog-card-body">
            <div class="blog-card-meta">
              <span>January 2, 2026</span>
              <span class="tag">Evaluations</span>
            </div>
            <h3><a href="/blog/understanding-fiie-texas.html">Understanding the FIIE: What Texas Parents Need to Know About Evaluations</a></h3>
            <p>A Full Individual Initial Evaluation is the gateway to special education services. Here's what gets tested, how long it takes, and what happens after.</p>
            <a class="read-more" href="/blog/understanding-fiie-texas.html">Read more &#8594;</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Card 3 -->
        <article class="blog-card" data-category="iep-goals">
          <div class="blog-card-image">🎯</div>
          <div class="blog-card-body">
            <div class="blog-card-meta">
              <span>December 18, 2025</span>
              <span class="tag">IEP Goals</span>
            </div>
            <h3><a href="/blog/how-to-write-measurable-iep-goals.html">How to Write Measurable IEP Goals (With Texas TEKS Alignment Examples)</a></h3>
            <p>Vague IEP goals lead to vague progress. Learn the formula for writing goals that are specific, measurable, and aligned to Texas standards.</p>
            <a class="read-more" href="/blog/how-to-write-measurable-iep-goals.html">Read more &#8594;</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Card 4 -->
        <article class="blog-card" data-category="parent-rights">
          <div class="blog-card-image">⚖️</div>
          <div class="blog-card-body">
            <div class="blog-card-meta">
              <span>December 10, 2025</span>
              <span class="tag">Parent Rights</span>
            </div>
            <h3><a href="/blog/texas-parent-rights-special-education.html">Your Rights as a Texas Special Education Parent: A Complete Guide</a></h3>
            <p>IDEA gives you powerful protections. Texas adds more. Here's a plain-language breakdown of every right you have — from consent to due process.</p>
            <a class="read-more" href="/blog/texas-parent-rights-special-education.html">Read more &#8594;</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Card 5 -->
        <article class="blog-card" data-category="ard-meetings">
          <div class="blog-card-image">📧</div>
          <div class="blog-card-body">
            <div class="blog-card-meta">
              <span>November 20, 2025</span>
              <span class="tag">ARD Meetings</span>
            </div>
            <h3><a href="/blog/how-to-disagree-at-ard-meeting.html">How to Disagree at an ARD Meeting Without Burning Bridges</a></h3>
            <p>You have the right to disagree — and you don't have to sign the IEP. Here's how to push back effectively while keeping the relationship constructive.</p>
            <a class="read-more" href="/blog/how-to-disagree-at-ard-meeting.html">Read more &#8594;</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Card 6 -->
        <article class="blog-card" data-category="evaluations">
          <div class="blog-card-image">🔍</div>
          <div class="blog-card-body">
            <div class="blog-card-meta">
              <span>November 5, 2025</span>
